	Tem um paper de um pessoal chinês que usou o NETLOGO (software de programação de modelagem de coisas multiagentes)
		Esse software já tem uma gridlock que permite simulações de cidades

Procurando mais sobre o NETLOGO, ele é bem interessante pra várias aplicações de sistemas multiagentes

Magnus Egerstedt (Georgia Tech)
	Tem uns projetos legais na área
		Mixed Autonomous and Non-Autonomous Vehicles in High-Complexity Traffic
		Sponsor: Ford Motor Company
		Duration: Jan. 2018 - Dec. 2019

		Project description: This project aims at understanding mixed groups of autonomous and non-autonomous vehicles in complex and unstructured traffic scenarios where the standard traffic rules are somewhat ambiguous and/or suspended, examples including parking lots, unregulated intersections, merging lanes, large traffic circles, etc. What this entails is the development of new autonomous driving behaviors that can predict and even mitigate human intentions based on a combination of distributed control, trust models, and machine learning. The expected outcomes are algorithms for autonomous driving that makes driving in high-complexity/low-structure environments more effective and safe. 
	Mais em:
	https://magnus.ece.gatech.edu/projects.html#DCIST

	https://magnus.ece.gatech.edu/index_projects.html

	Vários projetos com no âmbito de formação
